      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's exactly the point though. if it was just administrative delays, why were certain specific high-res images from that era suddenly categorized as 'restricted' for decades? i'm not talking about 'earthships' or anything crazy, i mean there's a very specific pattern of information being compartmentalized. if you look at how much funding shifted into 'black budget' aerospace projects right after 1969, it feels like they weren't just coming home, they were pivotting. can you help me look for any documented shifts in NASA's budget or project focus specifically in the months following the Apollo 11 landing? I want to see if there's any actual data that supports a sudden change in priority.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
